            <li><strong>4. FUNAI Admission Requirements for Direct Entry Students:</strong> Direct entry applicants to FUNAI must meet the following requirements:
                <ul class="child-ul">
                    <li>Possess at least two A-Level passes or equivalent qualifications.</li>
                    <li>Obtain a minimum of lower credit in relevant ND, NCE, or HND programs.</li>
                    <li>Provide a transcript from the previous institution (if applicable).</li>
                    <li>Participate in FUNAI’s direct entry screening exercise.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            
            <li><strong>5. FUNAI Cut-Off Marks for Post UTME:</strong> The general cut-off mark for FUNAI’s Post UTME is 150 for most programs. However, specific courses such as Medicine, Law, and Engineering may have higher cut-off marks:
                <ul class="child-ul">
                    <li>Medicine: 250</li>
                    <li>Law: 240</li>
                    <li>Engineering: 200</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            
